Description: Michael Kelly 1953 Telecaster in Black Vapor Just the right amount of vintage magic makes the 1953 the choice for those that are seeking a more traditional instrument. The '53s all-Alder body is capped with flame maple and the pickup configuration is vintage traditional. I have made a bunch of great modifications to this guitar. I replaced the neck pickup (original was very dull) with a Dimarzio True Velvet T. I added locking tuners, replaced the bridge saddles with Graphtech saddles, and also replaced the electronics with an Emerson kit. The switching is Bridge, Bridge & Neck (Series), Neck, Neck and Bridge (Parallel) so you get a ton of versatility. This will also come with a Levys Carmine Street Guitars gig bag. Get over $200 worth of extras for free. The action is set nice and low. It is strung with Elixir 10-46 strings. Please ask any questions before bidding and good luck.
